},{"content":"Add wine and, without measuring cup, cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add browned duck pieces, tomatoes, flour, cinnamon, stock cube, rosemary, bay leaves, sugar, salt and pepper then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <b>60 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Check tenderness of meat and if desired, continue cooking, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, <b>5-10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Meanwhile, cook pasta."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pasta"},{"content":"Bring a large saucepan of water with salt added to the boil. Cook paccheri according to packet instructions, or until al dente. Drain using a colander then transfer to a serving bowl."},{"content":"Ladle ragù over cooked pasta, sprinkle with reserved Parmesan and serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This rich, comforting ragù is from the Venetian islands and is traditionally eaten during winter months – one of the few meat dishes in a region famed for its fresh seafood. A perfect main course option for a winter dinner party when you really want to impress, the duck simmers slowly in the Thermomix with the blades gently rotating, resulting in a thick, flavourful sauce with meat that simply melts in the mouth."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 40m","6 portions"]}